definition: to turn back/to put back/reversal/melodic inversion (in music)
see 轉文|转文[zhuai3 wen2]
to revolve/to turn/to circle about/to walk about/classifier for revolutions (per minute etc): revs, rpm/classifier for repeated actions
to turn/to change direction/to transfer/to forward (mail)
to circle/to go back/to turn around/to answer/to return/to revolve/Hui ethnic group (Chinese Muslims)/time/classifier for acts of a play/section or chapter (of a classic book)

sentences.english: He spread a net for my feet and turned me back.
sentences.chinese: 他鋪下網羅，絆我的腳，使我轉回。

sentences.english: Ahsoka looked up shortly, her gaze bouncing back from the white armoured back like a thief.
sentences.chinese: 阿索卡將視線轉回白甲背影，小偷似的瞄了一下。

sentences.english: The above example jumps back to the beginning of a file. If you don't want to go back quite all the way -- let's say a kilobyte into it -- then you just write
sentences.chinese: 以上示例將跳轉回文件的開頭。

sentences.english: Those who enter the PhD Program without a master degree may return to the Master Program upon the approval of the Institute Faculty Meeting.
sentences.chinese: 逕修讀博士班者，經務會議同意，可轉回碩士班就讀。

sentences.english: Return to your test page and try to drop the button onto the column tag again.
sentences.chinese: 轉回至測試頁面，並再次嘗試將按鈕拖到列標籤上。

sentences.english: They return at evening: they make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city.
sentences.chinese: 他們晚上轉回，叫號如狗，圍城繞行。

sentences.english: None who go to her return or attain the paths of life.
sentences.chinese: 凡到她那裏去的不得轉回，也得不着生命的路。

sentences.english: What satirizes , this regeneration punctured the human to return the vision Holland.
sentences.chinese: 諷刺的是，這回熱刺人又把目光轉回了荷蘭。

sentences.english: Haku turns back to his boy form, but he is still very ill.
sentences.chinese: 白轉回到他的男孩，但是他仍然十分虐待。

sentences.english: Another is to look at the image cross-eyed and then shift back to normal vision.
sentences.chinese: 第二種方法是斜着看圖，然後轉回到正常視角。

sentences.english: Eli returns and Teri hides the phone again.
sentences.chinese: 伊菜又折轉回木屋中來，泰瑞也再次將手機藏了起來。

sentences.english: When they turned back into the wilderness they found none.
sentences.chinese: 當他們轉回往曠野去的時候，就沒有了。

sentences.english: Truth Is Lacking, And Whoever Turns From Evil Is Despoiled.
sentences.chinese: 真相越來越少，而那些個從邪惡裏轉回的人被掠奪了。

sentences.english: None that go unto her return again, neither take they hold of the paths of life.
sentences.chinese: 凡到他那裏去的不得轉回，也得不着生命的路。

sentences.english: Let's go back to that crossroad.
sentences.chinese: 我們轉回到那個十字路口吧。

sentences.english: There would be a loud "thud", and then he would swerve back on the road.
sentences.chinese: 聽到“砰“的一聲之後他再轉回路上正常行駛。
